Package: fhlus
Title: Fair Housing Land Use Score Calculation
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Aaron Barrall",, email = "aaronbarrall@ucla.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: Calculate the Fair Housing Land Use Score (FHLUS), a statistical measure
    that analyzes the spatial distribution of housing units (or other variables) across
    geographic areas ranked by opportunity indicators (e.g., income, poverty rate).
    The score normalizes the Area Under the Curve (AUC) to range from -1 (most
    concentrated in lowest-opportunity areas) to +1 (most concentrated in
    highest-opportunity areas). 
